         <div type="poem">
            <head type="title">ANTHEM FOR DOOMED YOUTH</head>

<lg><l n="1">WHAT passing-bells for these who die as cattle?</l>
            <l n="2" rend="indent">Only the monstrous anger of the guns.</l>
            <l n="3" rend="indent">Only the stuttering rifles' rapid rattle</l>
    <l n="4">Can patter out their hasty orisons.</l>
    <l n="5">No mockeries for them; no prayers nor bells,</l>
    <l n="6">Nor any voice of mourning save the choirs,â€”</l>
    <l n="7">The shrill, demented choirs of wailing shells;</l>
    <l n="8">And bugles calling for them from sad shires.</l>
               </lg>
         
 <lg><l n="9">What candles may be held to speed them all?</l>
    <l n="10" rend="indent">Not in the hands of boys, but in their eyes</l>
    <l n="11">Shall shine the holy glimmers of goodbyes.</l>
    <l n="12" rend="indent">The pallor of girls' brows shall be their pall;</l>
    <l n="13">Their flowers the tenderness of patient minds,</l>
    <l n="14">And each slow dusk a drawing-down of blinds.</l>
 </lg>       
              
         </div>

         
